premise_source_doc_sentence: The drug nitroglycerin  (  GTN  )  is a formulation of the same chemical substance used as the explosive nitroglycerin .

Methylammonium nitrate , also known as PR-M  (  which stands for `` Potomac River -- Mono-methylamine nitrate ''  )  soon was seen as the possible path toward creating a low-cost blasting agent  (  water gel explosives  )  that might replace the explosives based on nitroglycerin  (  dynamites  )  .

Nitrate reductase  (  NAD  (  P  )  H  )   (  , assimilatory nitrate reductase , assimilatory NAD  (  P  )  H-nitrate reductase , NAD  (  P  )  H bispecific nitrate reductase , nitrate reductase  (  reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide  (  phosphate  )   )  , nitrate reductase NAD  (  P  )  H , NAD  (  P  )  H-nitrate reductase , nitrate reductase -LSB- NAD  (  P  )  H2 -RSB- , NAD  (  P  )  H2 : nitrate oxidoreductase  )  is an enzyme with systematic name nitrite : NAD  (  P  )  + oxidoreductase .

Nitrate reductase  (  NADPH  )   (  , assimilatory nitrate reductase , assimilatory reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate-nitrate reductase , NADPH-nitrate reductase , assimilatory NADPH-nitrate reductase , triphosphopyridine nucleotide-nitrate reductase , NADPH : nitrate reductase , nitrate reductase  (  NADPH2  )  , NADPH2 : nitrate oxidoreductase  )  is an enzyme with systematic name nitrite : NADP + oxidoreductase .
Nitroglycerin is in the nitrate family of medications .
